entry.def: If you describe a speech or piece of writing as gobbledygook, you are criticizing it for seeming like nonsense and being very technical or complicated.

example.ex: When he asked questions, the answers came back in Wall Street gobbledygook.
example.tran: 他但凡提出疑问，得到的回答全是华尔街的官样文章。

means.word_mean: 1. incomprehensible or pompous jargon of specialists
